$ Excel: View -> Window

table { ll

  New Window ☰ Opens another → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window[window] onto current → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook so that it's possible to work at different regions at the same time.
  Arrange All ☰ Lay all open windows out so that they are all visible
  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/View/Window/Freeze-Panes[Freeze Panes] ☰ Freeze a region (for example a row containing a header) so that it stays visible even if the rest of the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet is scrolled.
  Split ☰ Divide the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet (of the current → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window) into four regions, each of which can be scrolled individually
  Hide ☰ Hides the current window
  Unhide ☰ Shows list of hidden windows from which a window can be chosen to be shown (unhidden)

table }
